Commands to set up the git-pull-reboot.sh script and crontab

# vim... for Brian... pleeeease
$ sudo apt-get install vim

# Never mind this one...
# 1. In order for git pull to work, the local git repo must be configured with
#    a username and email.
#
# $ git config --global user.name "Anonymous Pi"
# $ git config --global user.email "ucbdosenet@gmail.com"

1. Symlink

$ sudo ln -s /home/pi/dosenet-raspberrypi/git-pull-reboot.sh /usr/local/bin/git-pull-reboot.sh

2. Crontab

$ sudo crontab -e

and add the following line:
*/5 * * * * git-pull-reboot.sh
